article.headline: Weber St. 74, CS Bakersfield 43
article.story: OGDEN, Utah (AP) -- Dezmon Harris scored 16 points and was perfect from behind the 3-point line as Weber State routed Cal State Bakersfield 71-43 Tuesday night. Harris was 5-for-6 from the field and made all four 3-pointers he attempted before leaving the game with 3:57 remaining after being fouled and landing hard on the floor. Kellen McCoy and Daviin Davis each added 13 for the Wildcats (4-6), who defeated the Roadrunners 61-56 in November. Trent Blakley led the Roadrunners (1-10) with 15 points. The Wildcats ended the first half on a 15-3 run during the final six minutes to lead 29-20 at halftime. Harris had seven points during the run and Davis had five while all three of CS Bakersfield's points came from the foul line. The Roadrunners didn't make a field goal in the last 8:36 of the half. Danny Johnson's jumper with 1:32 left in the game gave the Wildcats a 72-41 lead, the biggest of the game. The Wildcats also came up with 10 steals and five blocked shots in the game.
